lzh_formatted:
  title: 春寒次大虛韻
  author: 許琛
  language: lzh
  text: 銅壺滴瀝佛燈殘。萬壑松濤夜色寒。喚起十年塵土夢。擁爐新試小龍團。
korean:
  title: 춘한 차 대허운
  author: 허침
  language: kor
  text: |-
    구리병에 물은 떨고 부처 등불 꺼지고는
    만학 솔 물결에 밤빛은 차가워라
    티끌 흙 십년 꿈을 깨워서 일으키어
    새삼스레 화로 끼고 소룡단(좋은 차의 이름)을 시험하오
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_1460_010_0130&viewSync=OT
  footnotes: []
english:
  title: 'Spring Chill: Following the Rhymes of Daeheo'
  author: Heo Chim
  language: eng
  text: |-
    In the copper vessel, water drips and the Buddha lamp gutters low.
    Across ten thousand valleys, pine winds whisper—the night grows cold.
    I awaken from a decade of dusty dreams,
    And by the glowing brazier, I steep the finest dragon pearls anew.
  footnotes:
    - The 'dragon pearls' (소룡단, xiaolongzhu) refers to a premium rolled tea, whose name evokes both precious jade and the dragon motifs of imperial luxury.
    - The Buddha lamp suggests a Buddhist temple setting, lending a contemplative, spiritual dimension to the poem's meditation on time and memory.
